The paper proposes a method that converts text into images and applies CNN models for classification, which suggests that it belongs to the computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-categories. The method also extracts text features automatically, indicating that it may fall under machine learning (cs.LG) and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories. Finally, the paper's focus on sentiment and topic classification tasks suggests that it may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category.
